# Flutter UI Conventions

## Interactive Elements ‚Äî Use `HoverButton`

Every tappable element (button, chip, toggle, icon, row) should use the
`HoverButton` widget from `theme_provider.dart`. It provides:
- Hand cursor on hover
- Subtle accent-tinted background highlight (animated 120 ms)
- `onTap`, `onLongPress`, `tooltip`, `borderRadius`, `padding`

```dart
// ‚úÖ PREFERRED ‚Äî single widget, visual hover + cursor
HoverButton(
  onTap: _doSomething,
  borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(8),
  child: Container(/* your button visuals */),
)

// ‚úÖ With tooltip
HoverButton(
  onTap: _doSomething,
  tooltip: 'Refresh',
  child: Icon(Icons.refresh),
)

// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî no hover feedback
GestureDetector(
  onTap: _doSomething,
  child: Container(child: Text('Click me')),
)
```

**Exception:** Full-screen scrims / barriers used only to dismiss overlays do
NOT need hover feedback (they are dismissal zones, not buttons).

If a custom hover visual is needed (e.g. a colored border change), use
`MouseRegion(cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click, ...)` with `onEnter`/`onExit`
and `setState` directly. Always include `cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click`.

## Color Opacity

Use `.withValues(alpha: 0.5)` instead of the deprecated `.withOpacity(0.5)`.

## Linting

The project uses `analysis_options.yaml` at the **repo root** (not inside
`phonegentic/`). Key rules to respect:

- `always_specify_types` ‚Äî annotate all local variables, parameters, return types.
- `prefer_single_quotes` ‚Äî use `'` unless the string contains a single quote.
- `sort_constructors_first` ‚Äî constructors before fields/methods.
- `use_super_parameters` ‚Äî prefer `{super.key}` over `Key? key) : super(key: key)`.
- `unnecessary_getters_setters` ‚Äî expose fields directly when no logic is needed.

Run `flutter analyze` from `phonegentic/` before considering any change done.

